text: The antioxidant activities of other oils isolated from diverse Iranian plants were also assayed [ 48 , 49 ] . In both cases the activities were weak . The percentage inhibition of Salvia eremophila Boiss . oil was of about one third of that of BHT , in contrast to the methanolic extracts of the same plant , which presented activities comparable to that of BHT . The authors considered the absence of phenolic compounds in the oils responsible for such weak activity . α - Pinene , borneol , camphene and transcaryophyllene were the main components of the oil [ 48 ] . For the Psammogeton canescens ( DC . ) vatke oil the authors [ 49 ] also attributed the weak activity of the oils to the presence of β - bisabolene , apiole , α - pinene and dill apiole , all non - phenolic compounds .
